{{Expand French|Massacre de Psara|date=December 2009}}
{{Campaignbox Greek War of Independence}}
[[File:Gysis Nikolaos After the destruction of Psara.jpg|right|thumb|300px|''After the Destruction of Psara'' by [[Nikolaos Gyzis]].]]

{{see| Psara#Destruction of Psara}}

The '''Destruction of Psara''' or '''Holocaust of Psara''' was an event in which the [[Ottomans]] destroyed the civilian population of the [[Greece|Greek]] island of [[Psara]] on July 5, 1824.<ref>Brewer, D. ''The Greek War of Independence: The Struggle for Freedom from Ottoman Oppression and the Birth of the Modern Greek Nation''. Overlook Press, 2001, {{ISBN|1-58567-172-X}}, pp. 235-236.</ref><ref>[http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k69788j/f262.table Gallica - French National Library]</ref> According to [[George Finlay]], the entire population of the island Psara before the massacre was about 7,000.<ref>Finlay, George. ''History of the Greek Revolution and the Reign of King Otho'' (edited by H.F. Tozer). Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1877 (Reprint: London 1971), {{ISBN|0-900834-12-9}}, p. 152.</ref>

