{{Orphan|date=October 2017}}

'''Dubthaigh''' or '''O'Dubthaigh''' is the name of an [[Ireland|Irish]] Tribe providing the origins of the name [[Duffy (surname)|Duffy]] or Duffie. The name means either "Dark Man" or "the one from the dark House", and embraces many of the famous clerics linked to [[Cong, County Mayo|Cong]], many of them called Saint Dubtach.

