'''Eurobandið''' (Euroband) is the name of [[Iceland]]ic technopop and dance duo [[Friðrik Ómar]] and [[Regína Ósk]], who together represented [[Iceland]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2008]] in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]]. They performed the song "[[This is My Life (Eurobandið song)|This Is My Life]]" in the second semi-final, on 22 May 2008 which won them a place in the final on May 24. They finished 14th out of 25 in the final with 64 points.

They have both, separately, established themselves as popular artists in Iceland and have tried to represent Iceland in [[Eurovision]] before as separate acts, but were unsuccessful. It was not until they joined that Iceland chose them as their representative in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2008]].

