{{unreferenced|date=December 2016}} {{Infobox Network | network_name = Heilongjiang Television (HLJTV) | network_logo = [[Image:Hljtv.png|150px|Heilongjiang Television]] | country = [[People's Republic of China]] | network_type = [[Terrestrial television|Broadcast]] | available = | website = [http://www.hljtv.com/ http://www.hljtv.com/] | }}
'''Heilongjiang Television ''' (HLJTV, {{zh|s=黑龙江电视台|t=黑龍江電視台|p=Hēilóngjiāng Diànshìtái}}), is a [[television network]] in the [[Harbin, China]] and [[Heilongjiang]] province area. The Heilongjiang Television and Radio Broadcast Center is located in the [[Long Ta]] (Dragon Tower). It is associated with [[Long Guang]] through the Heilongjiang Radio and TV Group. The logo is conspicuously both the English "H" and the Chinese "龙", depending on how one looks at it.
(Source: http://www.hljtv.com/dalou/main.htm)
==Online At Long Bei Jing Zai Xian== ''Heilongjiang Television Bei Jing Zai Xian'' ({{zh|c=黑龙江电视台背景在线}}) is the online website that describes the television stations of Heilongjiang Television, including the listing and contents. (The "Bei Jing" in this case means "background scenery" and is not the same as [[Beijing]], the capital city of [[China]]).
